The application was built on Spring Tool Suite platform using Microservices technology with JWT authentication and deployed on AWS Cloud and Postman Client in Google Chrome.

name: SecurityService
description: This is the micro-service in charge of the security of a JEE web application based on a SQL database (H2 or MySQL) that allows you to manage products classified by categories:  - The Backend part is based on two micro-services:       - A micro-service based on Spring IOC, Spring Data, Spring Data Rest, Spring Security JPA, Hibernate that allows you to manage products and categories. In this microservice, products and categories are stored in a NoSQL MongoDB database.       - An authentication micro-service that takes care of the security part based on Spring Security and Json Web Token (JWT). In this microservice, users and roles are stored in a SQL database (H2 or MySQL). MySQL in this case.  - The Frontend part is based on Angular
